	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tokumaru</b> [ Wed Feb 10, 2010 12:38 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">pivotman wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">well will the same problem happen with over clocking</div>
<br />Overclocking has been done, and it works up to a certain point. It seems that past this point the video memory can't keep up, and this also results in graphical glitches.
<br />
<br />Also keep in mind that all games that rely on timed code for visual effects (lots of 3D racing games, for example) will be completely broken, with overclocking or underclocking. So if you can, make your mod with a switch that allows switching back to the normal clock when you need to.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


