		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Won't it stop displaying correctly on a TV if you mess with the PPU's timing?</div>
<br />I guess so. The last person that overclocked the NES probably found a way to mess only with the CPU.
<br />
<br />EDIT: Found the <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=23085" class="postlink">thread</a>.
<br />
<br />EDIT: Oh yeah, overclocking the CPU screws up the music notes, because the CPU is responsible for generating sound.
<br />
<br />EDIT (again!): The page with the mentioned guide is gone, but it seems to be archived <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20041231032730/www.epicgaming.uk.ro/nes_oc/" class="postlink">here</a>.

		

